</div>

<div class="disclaimer">
  This site is an evolution of Jim Warner's extensive work researching and making available data regarding port buffers on network hardware. It is community maintained, and has no guarantee of correctness. If you have information to contribute, please submit a pull request or open an issue. <a href="https://github.com/buraglio/port-buffers">https://github.com/buraglio/port-buffers</a>. This is intended as a community resource, in keeping with the spirit of the original site. There will be inevitable mistakes, and we welcome corrections; please validate any results before relying on them for production use.  
  <br>
  <strong>Data quality note:</strong> Information here is by <em>rumor, innuendo, and extrapolation</em>.
  Manufacturers rarely publish packet buffer information in their data sheets. However, all data presented here is the result of data mining public resources, including vendor data sheets, white papers, and community discussions. 
  See the <a href="/summary/">summary page</a> for context on why buffers matter,
  or read about <a href="/concepts/microburst/">microbursts</a>.
</div>

<p style="font-size:0.85rem; color:#6c757d; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
  <strong>Shared memory</strong> means hardware permits buffers to be used by any port that needs them.
  In a shared memory design, it is not possible to let ALL memory go to queued packets
  (no room for new arrivals → head-of-line blocking).
  Some switches have multiple switch ICs, each managing their own memory pool — memory from one IC
  cannot be loaned to ports on another chip.
  <strong>Max TX buffer</strong> is the most a single queue/port can claim from the shared pool.
</p>

{%- set sections = switches | uniqueSections -%}

{% for section in sections %}
  {%- set rows = switches | whereSection(section) -%}

  <div class="section-header">
    {% if section == "Trident+" %}
      <a href="/concepts/trident-plus/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM56840, Shared Memory, 9 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Trident II" %}
      <a href="/concepts/trident-ii/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM56850/56854, Shared Memory, 12 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Mellanox" %}
      {{ section }} — Mellanox Spectrum ASIC, Shared Memory
    {% elif section == "Other Shared Memory" %}
      {{ section }} — Various ASICs
    {% elif section == "Large Queue 1RU" %}
      <a href="/concepts/deep-buffer/">{{ section }} Switches</a> — External DRAM, Very Large Buffers
    {% elif section == "Virtual Output Port (VoQ)" %}
      {{ section }} — Per-egress queues at ingress, eliminates head-of-line blocking
    {% elif section == "Trident 3" %}
      <a href="/concepts/broadcom-trident3/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM56870/BCM56771, Unified Shared Memory, 32 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Tomahawk" %}
      {{ section }} — Broadcom BCM56960/BCM56967, Shared Memory, 16 MB on-chip (4 pipes × 4 MB each; not unified)
    {% elif section == "Tomahawk 2" %}
      <a href="/concepts/broadcom-tomahawk2/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM56970, Unified Shared Memory, 42 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Trident 4" %}
      <a href="/concepts/broadcom-trident4/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM56880/BCM56780, Unified Shared Memory, up to 132 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Tomahawk 3" %}
      <a href="/concepts/broadcom-tomahawk3/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM56980, Unified Shared Memory, 64 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Tomahawk 4" %}
      <a href="/concepts/broadcom-tomahawk4/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM56990/BCM56993, Unified Shared Memory, 56.83–113.66 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Tomahawk 5" %}
      <a href="/concepts/broadcom-tomahawk5/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM78900/BCM78902, Unified Shared Memory, up to 165.2 MB on-chip
    {% elif section == "Broadcom Jericho" %}
      <a href="/concepts/broadcom-jericho/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM88670/BCM88675, VOQ + GDDR5 deep buffer, ~16 MB OCB
    {% elif section == "Broadcom Jericho2" %}
      <a href="/concepts/broadcom-jericho/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM88690/BCM88800, VOQ + 8 GB HBM, ~32 MB OCB
    {% elif section == "Broadcom Qumran" %}
      {{ section }} — Broadcom Access & Aggregation VOQ Deep Buffer (Qumran-MX, Qumran-AX)
    {% elif section == "Broadcom Qumran2c" %}
      <a href="/concepts/broadcom-qumran2c/">{{ section }}</a> — Broadcom BCM88820, VOQ + 4 GB HBM integrated deep buffer
    {% elif section == "Marvell OCTEON 10 (CN10K)" %}
      <a href="/concepts/marvell-octeon-cn10k/">{{ section }}</a> — Programmable NP/DPU; DDR5-backed packet buffer (16–48 GB per NP), no fixed on-chip SRAM pool
    {% elif section == "Marvell Prestera (MikroTik)" %}
      <a href="/concepts/marvell-prestera/">{{ section }}</a> — Marvell 98DX3236/98DX8216/98DX8525 (Aldrin2), Shared SRAM, ~1.5–8 MB estimated
    {% else %}
      {{ section }}
    {% endif %}
  </div>

  <div class="buffer-table-wrap">
    <table class="buffer-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Model</th>
          <th>Port Type</th>
          <th>RX Queue</th>
          <th>TX Queue</th>
          <th>Total Buffer</th>
          <th>RX Buffer</th>
          <th>TX Buffer</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for sw in rows %}
        <tr>
          <td class="model-cell">
            {% if sw.detail_page %}
              <a class="model-link" href="/switches/{{ sw.detail_page }}/">{{ sw.model }}</a>
            {% else %}
              {{ sw.model }}
            {% endif %}
          </td>
          <td>{{ sw.port_type or "" }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.rx_queue or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.tx_queue or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.total_buffer or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.rx_buffer or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td>{{ sw.tx_buffer or '<span class="empty">—</span>' | safe }}</td>
          <td class="notes-cell">{{ sw.notes or "" }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

{% endfor %}

<p style="margin-top:2rem; font-size:0.82rem; color:#6c757d;">
  To add or update a switch, edit <code>_data/switches.yaml</code>.
  Each switch is one YAML block. Add a <code>detail_page</code> slug to link to a page in <code>content/switches/</code>.
</p>
